HEADWORD: Fulham
<hw>Ful"ham</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[So named because
supposed to have been chiefly made at <etsep>Fulham</etsep>, in
Middlesex, Eng.]</ety> <def>A false die.</def> <mark>[Cant]</mark>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>fullam</asp>.]</altsp>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
